<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1663,1832]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1664,1688]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
Not a new record. Mak’s tentative identification is accompanied by a rather short diagnosis. Since 
<number box="[1380,1436,1663,1687]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1982.0">1982</number>
several new species of 
<taxonomicName box="[417,568,1700,1724]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Metavermilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[417,568,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Metavermilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been described, see overview in 
<bibRefCitation box="[1013,1228,1700,1724]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Nishi, E., Kupriyanova, E. &amp; Tachikawa, H. (2007) Metavermilia ogasawaraensis sp. nov. (Serpulidae: Sabellida: Polychaeta: Annelida) from deep-sea locations off Ogasawara Island, Japan with a literature overview of the genus. Zootaxa, 1447, 47 - 56." type="journal article">
Nishi 
<emphasis box="[1083,1141,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1158,1220,1700,1724]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="2007.0">2007</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. As mentioned by Mak, the yellowish horny distal cap of the operculum is unlike 
<taxonomicName box="[880,992,1736,1760]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Metavermilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="inflata">
<emphasis box="[880,992,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. inflata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and in the light of present knowledge might indicate that he had a juvenile specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sun, 1998" authorityName="Sun" authorityYear="1998" box="[711,1006,1772,1796]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Metavermilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="nanshaensis">
<emphasis box="[711,885,1772,1796]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. nanshaensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sun" box="[892,1006,1772,1796]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Sun, R. P. (1998) The Polynoidae, Eunicidae and Serpulidae (Annelida: Polychaeta) from Nansha Islands and adjacent waters. In: The Multidisciplinary Oceanographic Expedition Team of Academia Sinica to Nansha (eds.), Studies on marine fauna and flora and biogeography of the Nansha Islands and neighbouring waters. III. Contribution 2942 from the Institute of Oceanology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, 79 - 114." type="journal article" year="1998">
Sun, 
<quantity box="[950,1006,1772,1796]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.07492" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="in" value="1998.0">1998</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in hand. More material and a description of the tube are needed for a reliable identification.
</paragraph>
